  "body": "Gluster provisioner has a parameter:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    ....\r\n     volumetype: \"replicate:2\"\r\n```\r\nThis should override the default value when a volume is dynamically provisioned, but it doesn't seem to be working, the volume fails on a 2 node cluster and the heketi logs reveal that the hard coded constant value for replicaCount is being used.\r\n\r\n```\r\nJan 12 15:05:28 glusterclient2 heketi: [heketi] DEBUG 2017/01/12 15:05:28 /src/github.com/heketi/heketi/apps/glusterfs/volume_entry.go:89: [e06774ef9feccf8c292f6b7c94c0cfac] Replica 3\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like we are building the volumeDurabilityInfo api object in the parse params but never using it, we always pass in the hard coded values.\r\n\r\naround line 713\r\n```\r\nvolumeReq := &gapi.VolumeCreateRequest{Size: sz, Clusters: clusterIds, Gid: gid64, Durability: gapi.VolumeDurabilityInfo{Type: durabilityType, Replicate: gapi.ReplicaDurability{Replica: replicaCount}}}\r\n```",
